article.description: Randy Miller, Jr. registered 18 points as North Carolina Central defeated Delaware State 75-57 in the quarterfinals of the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference Tournament on Thursday night.
article.headline: Miller leads NC Central over Delaware State 75-57 in MEAC
article.linkText: Miller leads NC Central over Delaware State 75-57 in MEAC
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Randy Miller, Jr. registered 18 points as North Carolina Central defeated Delaware State 75-57 in the quarterfinals of the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference Tournament on Thursday night. Jibri Blount had 10 points for NC Central (16-15). Larry McKnight Jr. added 10 points. Raasean Davis had 10 points for NC Central. Kevin Larkin had 16 points for the Hornets (6-25). Saleik Edwards added 13 points. Johquin Wiley had six rebounds. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
